<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I suggest making a level 1 crit dump some wis or int gear on him and master him if you have already went over the 200 mark in another trade. I also suggest you do it SOON. VI has already implemented some trivial changes on the test server for trades that will lower a lot of combines thus making it a LOT harder to raise the skill. Level one characters can master all the way to 250 in pottery. 

This next statement is not meant to rub anyones hair the wrong way. So please don't take it that way. But I would not pay this ridiculus price people are asking for any new Trade skill made item. For the cost of one piece at the current prices you can almost master any trade skill. Yes it it takes some time. But so does getting any new item they add in game. When you see how easy it is to raise a trade you will agree. heck I mastered pottery in one day in a few hours. 

There will be some Master Potters who are gonna disagree with me but try it yourself and see. 

